       <div class="single_blog_wrap" style="width: 100% !important;"> 
        <div class="post_title"> 
         <h1>New Advising Initiatives Benefit Green River Students </h1> 
         <p class="posted-by-text"><span>By:</span> <a href="mailto:aqaasimgreenriver.edu">Andaiye Qaasim, Advisor</a></p> 
        </div>
        <!-- end post_title --> 
        <div class="post_content"> 
         <div class="post_photo_horizontal right"> 
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zn2-ehjyL-4&amp;list=PLVWolWHdWd1G0CAj1v6HM6hCyUmOUj4QP"><img alt="Lunch Byte workshop on immigration." src="images/lunch-byte-immigration-workshop.jpg"></a> 
         </div>
         <!-- end post_photo --> 
         <p><strong>Student advising is a critical component to student retention and academic success on campus. We are committed to a student centered approach. In keeping with this commitment, we are pleased to announce several changes to our advising model for the 2014-2015 academic year. </strong> </p> 
         <ol> 
          <li><strong>Integrated Degree Planning with Foundations for Success -</strong> This is the first year that the advising team will collaborate with the Foundations for Success (FFS) team on degree planning. The Foundation for Success program is required for all incoming academic students and all students enrolled in the Intensive English Language Program. FFS is a one-quarter program that helps students establish a strong learning foundation and enables them to transfer to top universities, while working alongside their Peer Mentors. This quarter, the FFS cohorts are divided by major. This will allow IP advisors to meet with their designated FFS cohort and work on specialized degree planning.</li> 
          <li><strong>Global Tea - </strong> Students can access their advisor on a regular basis at Global Tea Tuesdays. We offer tea, treats, and conversation. Global Teas are an excellent opportunity for students to connect with their peers and engage with their advisors in a relaxed and informal setting. We have been pleased with the overwhelming popularity of our Global Tea sessions.</li> 
          <li><strong>Lunch Byte - </strong> Lunch Byte presentations include free lunch and a workshop on timely topics. Students are equipped with the skills and knowledge needed to achieve academic success. Lunch Byte topics for winter quarter include university transfer, resume and cover letter writing skills, tips for writing your personal statement, career exploration, life skills, stress reduction, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zn2-ehjyL-4" title="Immigration workshop on YouTube">immigration</a> and tips for working in the United States. </li> 
          <li><strong>Transfer Workshops - </strong>University representatives are invited to Green River to give a presentation on transfer pathways, and admissions for International Students. Last quarter, we hosted Arizona State University, Iowa University, the University of Minnesota, the University of California (Davis and Irvine), and California State Long Beach. This quarter we look forward to hosting University of Nevada Las Vegas, Embry Riddle, Seattle University, as well as several more schools (to be announced in the coming weeks). </li> 
         </ol> 
         <p>We are thrilled to work with the talented and diverse group of students that we get a chance to serve each and every day. We look forward to getting to know each incoming class, and as always, remain committed to our student centered approach. </p> 
         <div class="post_photo_wide_banner"> 
          <img alt="Students enjoy tea, cookies and conversation with advisors at Global Tea" src="images/global-tea.jpg">
          <br> 
          <p>Students enjoy tea, cookies and conversation with advisors at Global Tea.</p>
         </div> 
